title: Grateful Dead Live at Santa Fe Downs on 1983-09-11
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Dire Wolf, Hell In A Bucket, West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, CC Rider-> Might As Well

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Let It Grow-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wang Dang Doodle-> Morning Dew-> Around & Around-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
sweet sloppy shredding this second set is the epitome of 83

one of the scorchingest Help Slips and relatively low on the flub scale for the era

a really fiery 2nd set Let it Grow

Wang Dang swaggers in, falls apart on Bob's mic issues, then blows the fuck up when Jerry goes ape out of nowhere - you may doubt it but yes Wang Dang Doodle is a gonzo highlight here

but then the Dew doesn't totally elevate at the end the way you hear it in your head so people critique the set for that reason

come onnnnnnnn maaaaaaaannnn get it together

anyway this is a really great fun set and and representative for the year in a goofy kinda way

Can't say too much grabbed my ear from set 1 but that's ok

To The Blue Sky People Again Those Magnetic Fields. Dipolar Energies From The Earth's Core. The Earth Itself Acting As A Giant Spherical Magnet. Manifesting Through The Nearby Sangre de Cristo Mountains. To The North,Over The Colorado Border.  Is Sisnaajini (Sierra Blanca.) The Eastern Border Of The World. Just Beyond, Near The Sand Dunes Of The San Luis Lakes,Lies Sipapu. Where The First Human Beings Emerged From The Earth... (Nice Upgrade Of A Great Show.Thanks To Dave Usborne.)

Not Perfect...but damn close This is one of many powerful shows from the memorable fall 83 tour.  And this is as good a remix/mastering as you'll get!  I definitely appreciate the extra time and know-how that goes into such fine audio production!  Thank you.
